  "doc_id": "e233f00f49834a21b19f4bdcef2677e7",
  "text": "# OPENING AN ACCOUNT  \n**Q: What's the quickest way to open an account?**\nA: Online at www.firstuk.bank/open-account (1–2 business days).  \n**Q: Can I open an account in a branch?**\nA: Yes. Visit any FirstUK branch and staff will help you (usually same day or next day).  \n**Q: Can I open an account by post?**\nA: Yes. Call 0800-555-2265 to request the postal application pack (5–7 business days).  \n**Q: What identification do I need?**\nA: UK Passport or Driving License (original or certified copy).  \n**Q: What address proof do I need?**\nA: Utility bill, council tax letter, or bank statement (dated within 3 months).  \n**Q: How old do I need to be?**\nA: 18 years old (minimum age for retail banking accounts).  \n**Q: What if I can't provide these documents?**\nA: Contact us at support@firstuk.bank — we may be able to help with alternative verification.  \n---",
